In [364]:
holidays['is_holiday'] = ~holidays['type'].isnull()
holidays['is_transferred_holiday'] = holidays['transferred']
holidays['is_holiday'] = holidays['is_holiday'] & ~holidays['is_transferred_holiday']
holiday_type_dummies = pd.get_dummies(holidays['type'], prefix='holiday_type')
holidays = pd.concat([holidays, holiday_type_dummies], axis=1)
holidays['is_national_holiday'] = holidays['locale'] == 'National'

Test Prep:¶

In [381]:
# Convert 'date' columns in both datasets to datetime
test['date'] = pd.to_datetime(test['date'])
transactions['date'] = pd.to_datetime(transactions['date'])

# Merge test data with transactions
merged_test = pd.merge(test, stores, on='store_nbr', how='left')
merged_test = pd.merge(merged_test, transactions, on=['date', 'store_nbr'], how='left')

# Merge with holidays and oil datasets
holidays['date'] = pd.to_datetime(holidays['date'])
oil['date'] = pd.to_datetime(oil['date'])
merged_test = pd.merge(merged_test, holidays, on='date', how='left')
merged_test = pd.merge(merged_test, oil, on='date', how='left')
# Forward-fill and backward-fill missing oil prices
merged_test['dcoilwtico'] = merged_test['dcoilwtico'].ffill().bfill()

# Handle holiday information
merged_test['is_holiday'] = merged_test['is_holiday'].fillna(0)

# Feature engineering for temporal features
merged_test['year'] = merged_test['date'].dt.year
merged_test['month'] = merged_test['date'].dt.month
merged_test['day'] = merged_test['date'].dt.day
merged_test['day_of_week'] = merged_test['date'].dt.dayofweek
merged_test['week_of_year'] = merged_test['date'].dt.isocalendar().week
merged_test['quarter'] = merged_test['date'].dt.quarter
merged_test['is_weekend'] = merged_test['day_of_week'].isin([5, 6])  # Boolean flag for weekend
merged_test['is_month_start'] = merged_test['date'].dt.is_month_start
merged_test['is_month_end'] = merged_test['date'].dt.is_month_end

# Drop unnecessary columns
merged_test.drop(columns=['type_y', 'locale', 'locale_name', 'description',
                          'transferred', 'is_transferred_holiday', 
                          'holiday_type_Additional', 'holiday_type_Bridge',
                          'holiday_type_Event', 'holiday_type_Holiday',
                          'holiday_type_Transfer', 'holiday_type_Work Day', 
                          'is_national_holiday', 'transactions'], inplace=True, errors='ignore')

# Lag features for oil price (similar to train data)
merged_test['dcoilwtico_lag_1'] = merged_test.groupby('store_nbr')['dcoilwtico'].shift(1)
merged_test['dcoilwtico_lag_2'] = merged_test.groupby('store_nbr')['dcoilwtico'].shift(2)

# Fill missing values in lagged features
merged_test['dcoilwtico_lag_1'] = merged_test['dcoilwtico_lag_1'].ffill().bfill()
merged_test['dcoilwtico_lag_2'] = merged_test['dcoilwtico_lag_2'].ffill().bfill()

# For the test set, sales lag features are not available, so set them to 0
merged_test['sales_lag_1'] = 0
merged_test['sales_lag_2'] = 0

# Scaling lag features using the same scaler as the train set
scaled_columns = ['dcoilwtico', 'dcoilwtico_lag_1', 'dcoilwtico_lag_2', 'sales_lag_1', 'sales_lag_2']
merged_test[scaled_columns] = scaler.transform(merged_test[scaled_columns])

# Preserve 'id' for final output
ids_test = merged_test['id']
X_test = merged_test.drop(columns=['id'])

# One-hot encode categorical variables for the test set
X_test = pd.get_dummies(X_test)

# Align test set to match the training set columns
X_test = X_test.reindex(columns=X_train.columns, fill_value=0)

# Ensure no missing values
X_test = X_test.fillna(0)

# Confirm alignment
assert list(X_train.columns) == list(X_test.columns), "Columns of X_train and X_test are not aligned!"

#Store & Sales Heat Map 
def geocode(city, state):
    geolocator = Nominatim(user_agent="store_sales_map")
    try:
        location = geolocator.geocode(f"{city}, {state}")
        if location:
            return location.latitude, location.longitude
        else:
            return None, None
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Error geocoding {city}, {state}: {e}")
        return None, None

#adding long & lat for each store 
stores['latitude'], stores['longitude'] = zip(*stores.apply(lambda row: geocode(row['city'], row['state']), axis=1))
time.sleep(1) #pause for geocode
store_sales = train.groupby('store_nbr')['sales'].sum().reset_index() #aggregating sales by store
merged_data = pd.merge(stores, store_sales, on='store_nbr', how='left') #merging sales & stores
